observations.recommendation:
We recommended and Management agreed, through the MENRO, to:
a. review the Programs under each strategy for viability, and if warranted, revise the plan to ensure doability and sustainability, taking into consideration the possible hindrances on non-implementation. In addition, check the budget allocation for each program to ensure that enough resources are given to every program;
b. revisit, evaluate, and assess the Municipal Government’s presently adopted SWMP and have the same aligned with that of the one approved by the authority;
c. evaluate the reliability of the perimeter enclosures and assess whether or not a new and much stable fence should be constructed in order to discourage easy access both by animals and the people in the area; and
d. strictly limit the access of any individual in the landfill premises by requiring each visitor to log in their information for monitoring purposes.

We recommended and Management agreed, through the LSB, to improve the processes of planning, prioritization and budgeting of SEF through:
a. instituting measures to make the LSB more proactive and effective in introducing educational reforms within its capacity;
b. the formulation of development programs on education for the Municipal Government, articulating the collective vision of the major stakeholders;
c. strictly requiring the submission of the respective schools’ budget proposals together with their annual appropriations from the national government to be able to properly identify the items for funding augmentation; hence, items for funding were based only on
d. creation of an ad hoc Technical Working Group (TWG) to spearhead the evaluation and prioritization of the submitted proposals, specifically the viability of the each planned PPAs;
e. strict observance of the requirement set forth by the law, specifically Section 7 (b) of the Republic Act No. 10410 by allocating adequate funds for the implementation of the ECCD Programs;
f. improve the payment process through adoption of a more efficient flow of documents. Also, if necessary, adopt measures as regards to the notification issues whenever a problem arises or a deficiency, if any, will be noted while the documents are on the process for approval;
g. consider the early preparation and approval of the SEF budget in adherence to the timeline and procedures on budget preparation of the Municipality, to avoid eventual delays in the implementation of PPAs; and
h. monitor on a periodic basis the status of implementation of SEF PPAs, by conducting regular LSB meetings to address the issues and concerns affecting the proper and timely implementation thereof.

We recommended and Management agreed, through the LSB and the Municipal Planning Development Office (MPDO), hasten the development of measures, within its capacity, to assess projects, activities and programs with respect not only to the desired outputs, but as well to the outcomes and impacts these projects have to the locality.

We recommended and Management agreed, through the MENRO, to:
1. review the Programs for viability, and if warranted, revise the plan to ensure doability and sustainability, taking into consideration the possible hindrances on non-implementation. In addition, check the budget allocation for each program to ensure that enough resources are given to every program; and
2. revisit, evaluate, and assess the Municipal Government’s presently adopted SWMP and have the same aligned with that of the one approved by the authority;
3. closely monitor the processes and protocols being adopted by the six (6) barangays allowed by the MENRO to collect, transport and dump their solid waste in the landfill to ensure that proper procedures thereto are being followed;
4. exert extra effort in monitoring the Municipal Government compliance with Laws, Rules and Regulations with regards to Solid Waste Management;
5. regularly monitor the usage and availability of personnel protective gears, and if needed, consider purchasing new ones to ensure the safety of each personnel involved in waste management. Additionally, as a control measure, encourage each personnel to wear the necessary protective gears and equipment in line with their duties, and provide appropriate disciplinary actions to those who failed to wear one;
6. evaluate the reliability of the perimeter enclosures and assess whether or not a new and much stable fence should be constructed in order to discourage easy access both by animals and the people in the area;
7. strictly limit the access of any individual in the landfill premises by requiring each visitor to log in their information for monitoring purposes; and
8. consider drafting a policy and/or guideline on the wearing of protective gears and equipment for visitors, wastes pickers/scavengers and personnel whenever they are within the vicinity.

In order to address the observations increase collections, we recommended that the Municipal Treasurer:
1. Improve revenue forecasting by the tools provided by the Bureau of Local Government Finance (BLGF);
2. Inspect Fully business Implemented establishments within the jurisdiction of the Municipality to ensure effective and efficient collection of business taxes as mandated under [Section 470 (d)(4)] of LGC;
3. Maintain and update the tax information system of the Municipality thru:
 establishin g a tax roll for each type of tax and revenue imposed in the Revenue Code;
 conduct of tax census and develop revenue data bank; and
 maintainin g a systematic and organized records of payments of all taxpayers.
4. Furnish the Accountant the complete and Implemented accurate list of taxpayers with the corresponding amount of taxes due and collectibles for the year as basis to record the correct Real Property Tax (RPT) and Special Education Tax (SET) Receivables in the books; and
5. Institute measures and strategies to efficiently collect various revenues provided under the Revenue Code of the Municipality, such as:
 sending of tax/revenu e bills to taxpayers;
 thorough monitoring of payment of taxpayers and identificati on and collection of tax delinquenc ies; and
 Strict implementa tion of sanctions and penalties on erring taxpayers.
6. Correct the coding of Fully revenue Implemented accounts to align and conform to the prescribed PPSAS Revised Chart of Accounts for LGUs.

Observe proper treatment and classification of accounts;

Ensure judicious and careful planning by the Local Finance Committee in preparing the Annual Budget so that they will not exceed the approved budget.

Monitor the expenditures to ensure that proper accounting treatment is observed.
